{#def name, value="", placeholder="", type="text", required=false, extra="", radius="md", autocomplete="", minlength=0 #}
{#
  Styled <input>. Matches the focus-ring token used across the app. Usage:
    <TextInput name="email" type="email" placeholder="you@example.com" required />

  ``radius`` is "md" (the in-workspace default) or "lg" (the auth cards
  use the larger radius). ``autocomplete`` and ``minlength`` are
  pass-throughs for forms that need them.

  Any other HTML attribute (id=, readonly, data-*, onclick=) flows
  through via JinjaX's ``attrs`` passthrough. The visual shell
  (border, padding, text size, focus ring) comes from the shared
  ``INPUT_BASE`` catalog global (see templates.py) so TextInput,
  Select and Textarea share one source of truth for the focus token.
#}
{%- set _cls = "w-full " ~ INPUT_BASE ~ " rounded-" ~ radius ~ " " ~ extra -%}
<input {{ attrs.render(
  type=type,
  name=name,
  value=value,
  placeholder=placeholder,
  required=required,
  autocomplete=autocomplete or False,
  minlength=minlength or False,
  classes=_cls,
) }}>
